The paper deals with the synthesis of systems that optimize a given specification under probabilistic assumptions about the inputs. This involves the use of automata theory, Markov chains, and decision processes, which are all topics that are commonly studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
